						               													<description>Aromat is an abstract strategy game that uses a mobile app for score calculation and score keeping. The heart of the game is the hexagonal game tile, consisting of shapes, numbers, dots and a player Emblem Sign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can play Aromat by placing the Game Tiles next to each other. Each special calculation created by the two adjacent sides of the Tiles following the gameplay rules either adds or subtracts a certain amount of points to your Game Score. The mobile app does the score calculation and score keeping for you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Aromat can be played using Play Field Elements by constructing these elements before the game starts. It can also be played without, which requires more thinking because of the many possibilities present in any given moment during gameplay. Therefore it is recommended to use the Play Field Elements until a player becomes strategically aware of the many possibilities the game has to offer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Research in neuroscience, human behavior and interaction and music didactics has been conducted in order to construct the methods and mechanisms behind Aromat. It contains beneficial aspects in terms of brain training and musicality training, which are achieved in a fun and engaging way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Aromat is a collectible game that starts out with the &amp;quot;Basic Set&amp;quot; and expands through a system of &amp;quot;Extension Sets&amp;quot;'&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
